Package: BulkSignalR
Type: Package
Title: Infer Ligand-Receptor Interactions from Bulk Transcriptomic or Proteomic Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jacques","Colinge",email="jacques.colinge@inserm.fr",role="aut"),
    person("Simon","Cabello-Aguilar",email="simon.cabello-aguilar@inserm.fr",role="cre"))
Description: Inference of ligand-receptor (LR) interactions from bulk
    (transcirptomic or proteomic) data. BulkSignalR bases its inferences
    on the LRdb database included in our other package, SingleCellSignalR
    available from Bioconductor. It relies on a statistical model that
    is specific to bulk data sets. Different visualization and data
    summary functions are proposed to help navigating prediction results.
URL: https://github.com/jcolinge/BulkSignalR
BugReports: https://github.com/jcolinge/BulkSignalR/issues
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.6.1.0)
Imports:
    doParallel,
    foreach,
    multtest,
    igraph,
    SingleCellSignalR,
    dplyr,
    import
Suggests:
    ComplexHeatmap (>= 2.0.0),
    grid,
    limma (>= 3.0.0),
    edgeR (>= 3.0.0)
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
